com.interpss.core.aclf.adj

Interface TapControl

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BranchFlowControl, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAclfAdjustment, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TapControlImpl

    public interface TapControl
extends BranchFlowControl
    A representation of the model object 'Tap VControl'. TapControl is designed to use transformer tap (on the from side or the to side) to control a bus voltage or a branch Q flow. The bus could be the transformer's terminal bus or any bus in the network. The branch has to the transformer itself.

    The following features are supported:

    • Control Type
    • Tap Step Size
    • Tap Steps
    • Compensate Z
    • Vc Gen PV Bus
    • Vc Bus
    See Also:
    AclfAdjustPackage.getTapControl()

      • isVcGenPVBus

        boolean isVcGenPVBus()
        Returns the value of the 'Vc Gen PV Bus' attribute. The default value is "false". the Voltage Control bus is a generator PV bus. In this case, TapControl only becomes effective when the PV bus is inactive because of gen QLimit violation.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Vc Gen PV Bus' attribute.
